Actian 4GL OpenROAD Assignment Statements use error trapping mechanisms to handle errors during execution. For instance, if a variable is not defined before being used, the language will raise an error and stop executing. Here's an example:
```
TRY
  undefined_variable = 'Hello';
CATCH Exception
  PRINT 'Error: Undefined Variable';
END-TRY;
```
This code attempts to assign a value to `undefined_variable`, which has not been declared before. The TRY-CATCH block will catch the error and print an error message.

